{% extends "view_base.jinja" %}
{% block title %}Bug Trail &mdash; Help{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<div class="container">
  <h1 class="h3 mb-3">Getting started with Bug Trail</h1>

  <p>
    Bug Trail is a local error logger. Your application writes log records to a SQLite
    database through the <code>bug_trail_core</code> handler; this server reads that database
    and displays a searchable record of every error, plus environment and system metadata.
    Keep this server running while you develop — the page auto-refreshes whenever new log
    records are written.
  </p>

  <h2 class="h5 mt-4">1. Register the handler in your app</h2>
  <pre><code>import logging
import bug_trail_core

config = bug_trail_core.read_config("pyproject.toml")
handler = bug_trail_core.BugTrailHandler(config.database_path)
handler.setLevel(logging.ERROR)

logger = logging.getLogger()     # root logger
logger.addHandler(handler)

# or, for a specific logger:
logger = logging.getLogger("myapp")
logger.addHandler(handler)</code></pre>

  <h2 class="h5 mt-4">2. Configure in <code>pyproject.toml</code> (optional)</h2>
  <pre><code>[tool.bug_trail]
app_name      = "myapp"              # used to derive default data paths
app_author    = "myteam"
database_path = "errors.db"          # path to the SQLite file
report_folder = "bug_trail_reports"  # legacy; unused by the live server
source_folder = ""                   # optional: path to source code</code></pre>
  <p class="text-muted small">
    If you skip <code>[tool.bug_trail]</code>, defaults come from <code>platformdirs</code>
    &mdash; which lands in your per-user data dir.
  </p>

  <h2 class="h5 mt-4">3. Start the server</h2>
  <pre><code>bug_trail start
# or with options:
bug_trail start --port 8080 --db /tmp/errors.db --host 0.0.0.0
bug_trail start --reload   # dev mode: restart server on code changes</code></pre>

  <h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Verify</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Visit <a href="/">the log list</a>.</li>
    <li>Run your app and trigger an error.</li>
    <li>This page should auto-refresh the moment the row is written.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Admin commands</h2>
  <pre><code>bug_trail admin clear   # wipe all rows, keep schema
bug_trail admin reset   # drop and recreate all tables</code></pre>
  <p>The same actions are available from the <a href="/admin">Admin</a> page.</p>
</div>
{% endblock %}
